  & [RequirementDelta] is the updated requirement shape
    + [delta] closed-class sense routing is now a policy surface with a default operational mode and explicit audit/query mode
    + [delta] future primer compaction should treat closed-class sense deferral as upstream evidence discipline, not as post-render filtering
    + [delta] future primer consumers must read compaction metadata before treating compact_evidence as exhaustive workspace evidence
    + [delta] future evidence output should choose a parseable namespace at projection boundaries rather than writing raw notes into refs
    + [delta] future support-producing diffusion passes should use ensure_support_record instead of direct support_records.push
    + [delta] future routing policy should consume WobbleFactorPrimer rather than relying only on aggregate wobble score
    + [delta] future actor resolution should convert implied actor uncertainty only with explicit provider or dialogue evidence
    + [delta] future relation taxonomy changes should preserve candidate_relation_ref and endpoint_decision_refs
    + [delta] future fixture implementation slices should implement the matrix cases without broadening into benchmark design
    + [delta] future uncertainty proposal types must define boundary criteria before entering SemanticGraph
    + [delta] future routing changes should add dimensions/factors rather than aggregate-only thresholds
    + [delta] future primer consumers must validate schema_id, schema_version, compatibility_floor, and required_fields before relying on field semantics
    + [delta] future regression scripts should prefer compact mode unless they explicitly need exhaustive evidence arrays
    + [delta] future snapshot and fixture slices should use slm_regression_harness.py as their proof route baseline
    + [delta] future accepted behavior changes that alter compact outputs should update golden snapshots deliberately through slm_golden_snapshot.py --update
    + [delta] future sidecar adapters must include the task_contract envelope field and must not treat sidecar ProviderSuggestion output as graph authority
    + [delta] future contradiction and arbitration work should consume jury measurements and cited_panel_refs rather than inferring disagreement severity from status alone
    + [delta] future contradiction-producing passes should use ensure_contradiction_record to keep repeated diffusion idempotent
    + [delta] future sidecar transports must call the validated parser or provide an equivalent rejection path before ingesting provider suggestions
    + [delta] future provider set configuration can reference mock, LM Studio, and Ollama adapters without adding live network execution
    + [delta] future provider selection should load ProviderSetConfig and validate capabilities before constructing live adapter calls
    + [delta] future lexical substrate changes should begin with rebuild_lexical_substrate_workflow.py --dry-run and only execute rebuilds intentionally
    + [delta] future lexical substrate distribution planning must preserve Open English WordNet CC-BY 4.0 attribution and distinguish generated artifacts from source authority
    + [delta] future stabilization changes must update threshold calibration fixtures when changing gate values or comparison semantics
